      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know there are lines i can call but it feels so performative. like, a stranger on the phone is just gonna give me some scripted speech about how things get better, but they don't understand. they don't understand that the person i was is actually gone. there's no \"getting back on track\" when the track itself has been destroyed. it just feels like i'm being forced to keep running a race i've already lost. it's not just sadness, it's like... total emptiness. like there's no point in even trying to fix it anymore.",
